\def RFE_WAIT_WAITTIMER_INDEX \brief RFE_WAIT_WAITTIMER_INDEX REF_WAIT_USEC uses the last PIT timer

\def RFE_WAIT_TICKS_ACCURACY \brief RFE_WAIT_TICKS_ABS_ACCURACY The accuracy of the wait in ticks in absolute ticks ( NOT a percentage or factor) set to <0.5uSec ( ( RFE_WAIT_TICKS_ABS_ACCURACY * 100ul ) / RFE_WAIT_TICKS_PER_USEC ) calculates the absolute accuracy in 0.01 uSec units

documentation.value: \def RFE_WAIT_TICKS \brief RFE_WAIT_TICKS waiting a specified number of perhipheral ticks \detail RFE_WAIT_TICKS : Wait the specified number of perhipheral ticks before continuing execution. The accuracy of the RFE_WAIT_TICKS is -0 and +RFE_WAIT_TICKS_ACCURACY ticks Due to FuSa timer access overhead, it will never be less be always a little longer then specified

code.value: \ if ( RFE_HW_PIT_MAX_USEC < ( USECWAIT ) ) { RFE_ERROR_SET( (rfe_error_parameterOutOfRange_e) ); } \ else if ( RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR ) {/* skip due to error*/ } else \ { RFE_WAIT_TICKS( ( USECWAIT ) * RFE_HW_PIT_TICKS_PER_USEC ) ; }

documentation.value: \def RFE_WAIT_USEC \brief RFE_WAIT_USEC support for waiting a specified number of microseconds \detail RFE_WAIT_USEC : Wait the specified number of microseconds before continuing execution. The accuracy of the WAIT is -0.0 and +0.3 microseconds Due to FuSa timer access overhead, it will never be less be always a little longer then specified Example: RFE_WAIT_USEC(12) this will wait ( in a short loop ) between 12.0 and 12.0 + ( (1.0 * RFE_WAIT_TICKS_ACCURACY ) / RFE_WAIT_TICKS_PER_USEC ) microseconds before continuing ( the 1.0 for a float value, otherwise the division is truncated to integer zero )

documentation.value: \def RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC \def RFE_WAIT_WHILE \def RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED \def RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED \brief RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( ..) { .... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE ; Is used to put a time limit on a do{ ..... } while( ) to prevent infinite loops Preventing an inifinite loop with an unknown number of instructions within the loop means this timelimit does NOT have to be as precise as the RFE_WAIT_USEC \detail do{ ..... } while( ) loops may be nested. Example: do{ ..do{ ..... } while( ) ... } while( ) Example: do{ .. functionx() ... } while( ) with functionx() containing a do{ ..... } while( ) When changing do{ ..... } while( ) loops into RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( ..) { .... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE ; There is a limit (7 deep) on the amount of nesting for timelimited RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( ..) { .... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE ; How to replace a do{ .... if ( some_expression) {condition=true;} ... } while( condition ) by a time limited loop : RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( 100ul ) { .... if (...) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ..... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE ; The loop will end when : '100 microseonds have passed' OR 'RFE_ERROR' was set OR 'RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED' was called To check what happened the user can check after the RFE_WAIT_WHILE : RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( 100ul ) { .... if (some_expression) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ..... Please note if (RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED ) would result in an error ! } RFE_WAIT_WHILE ; if (RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED) { ... RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED was called within the loop } if (RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR) { some where the RFE error was set } if ( (!(RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED)) && RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR) { a timeout occurred } Example of nested loop. Please note the the COMPLETION flags are local for a loop, see below do{ .... if ( some_expression1) {condition1=true;} ( *1 ) do{ .... if ( some_expression2) {condition2=true;} ( *2 ) ..... if ( some_expression3) {condition2=true;} ( *3 ) ... } while( condition2 ) ... if ( some_expression1) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ( *4 ) ... } while( condition1 ) ... RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( 100ul ){ .... if ( some_expression1) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ( *1 ) RFE_WAIT_DO_USEC( 80ul ){ .... if ( some_expression2) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ( *2 ) if ( some_expression3) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ( *3 ) ... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE; if (RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED) { ... RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED was called within the loop (*2 or *3) } if (RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR) { some where the RFE error was set } if ( (!(RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED)) && RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR) { a timeout occurred } ... if ( some_expression1) {RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED;} ( *4 ) ... } RFE_WAIT_WHILE; ... if (RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED) { ... RFE_WAIT_SETCOMPLETED was called within the loop *1 or *4 } if (RFE_ERROR_IS_ERROR) { some where the RFE error was set } if ( (!(RFE_WAIT_LASTENDEDWAITDOWHILE_WASCOMPLETED)) && RFE_ERROR_IS_NO_ERROR) { a timeout occurred }

\brief Initializes the unit Must have called rfeHwPit_init beforehand \param [inout] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER Error parameter. - Checks if PIT active, optionally - Initializes WAIT and nested WAITDO level timers
\brief Returns maximum nesting level for WAITDO loops \returns maximum nesting level for WAITDO loops

\brief Creates a new waitdo timer when available Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above \param [in] timeoutvalue the timeout value in ticks ( up to a little less then 1 uSec may be added due to setup-overhead ) \param [inout] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER Error parameter. Sets error on invalid timeout value or no availble timers

\brief Removes the last created waitdo timer. Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above \param [inout] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER Error parameter. Sets an error when no active waitdo timer

\brief Sets completion flag for the current waitdo timer Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above \param [inout] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER Error parameter. Sets an error when no active waitdo timer

\brief Tests if the last removed waitdo timer had its completion flag set Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above \return true: last removed waitdo timers completion flag was set false: last removed waitdo timers completion flag was NOT set

\brief Clears the waitdo timer completion flag set for any previous completed waitDo Prevents completion to stay true when a new Waitdo does not start due to errors Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above

\brief Tests if : 'the current waitdo completion flag was set' OR 'timeout' OR 'rfeError set' Do not call this function directly, only through the #defines above \param [inout] RFE_ERROR_FUNCTION_PARAMETER Error parameter. \return true: 'the current waitdo completion flag was NOT set' AND 'No timeout' AND 'rfeError not set'
